        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued October 18 at 8:57PM CDT by NWS Houston/Galveston TX</headline>
        <description>At 856 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Camp Creek Lake, or 19 miles northeast of Hearne, moving southeast at
25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Madisonville, Normangee, Iola, and North Zulch.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
